        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(discord): balance truncated progress italics",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n- Fixes Discord progress drafts that can show a literal leading underscore when an italic commentary line is truncated.\r\n- The shared progress-draft formatter now strips an unmatched leading italic delimiter after compaction, matching the existing unmatched-backtick protection.\r\n- Adds regression coverage for truncated commentary-style progress lines.\r\n\r\n## Linked context\r\nCloses #88895.\r\n\r\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\r\n- Behavior or issue addressed: Discord `streaming.mode: \"progress\"` commentary could render `_Checking...` literally when line compaction removed the closing `_`.\r\n- Real environment tested: local OpenClaw contributor checkout.\r\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: focused formatter regression in `src/plugin-sdk/channel-streaming.test.ts`.\r\n- Evidence after fix: the regression expects the truncated commentary line to render as `Checking whether the Discord progress draft keeps markdown…`, without a leading `_`.\r\n- Observed result after fix: focused Vitest shard passed.\r\n- What was not tested: live Discord guild progress-message edit flow.\r\n- Proof limitations or environment constraints: this contributor environment does not have a safe Discord bot/guild setup for live channel proof.\r\n\r\n## Tests and validation\r\n- `corepack pnpm exec oxfmt --write --threads=1 src/channels/streaming.ts src/plugin-sdk/channel-streaming.test.ts`\r\n- `PNPM_CONFIG_OFFLINE=true corepack pnpm test src/plugin-sdk/channel-streaming.test.ts -- --reporter=dot` passed 1 Vitest shard / 29 tests.\r\n- `git diff --check -- src/channels/streaming.ts src/plugin-sdk/channel-streaming.test.ts`\r\n\r\n## Risk checklist\r\n- User-visible behavior changed: Yes, only for compacted progress-draft text with unmatched leading italic underscores.\r\n- Config, environment, or migration behavior changed: No.\r\n- Security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior changed: No.\r\n- Highest-risk area: over-stripping underscores in compacted progress text. Mitigated by only stripping when the compacted output has an odd underscore count and starts with `_`, which matches the broken italic-commentary shape.\r\n\r\n## Current review state\r\nReady for maintainer review; no live Discord proof is available from this contributor environment.",
